of%20their%20assets%20in%20order%20to%20avoid%20conflicts%20of%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBondi%20was%20nominated%20by%20Trump%20to%20lead%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20after%20former%20Rep.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatt-gaetz-withdraws-attorney-general-consideration-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMatt%20Gaetz%20of%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%20withdrew%20from%20consideration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20confirmation%20hearings%20began%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20and%20she%20is%20widely%20expected%20to%20be%20successfully%20confirmed%20by%20the%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpam-bondi-truth-social-stock-lobbying-financial-disclosure-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737066968000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67897b2c2fcded5e9073918d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpam-bondi-truth-social-stock-lobbying-financial-disclosure-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bondi%2C%20who's%20been%20working%20as%20a%20lobbyist%20and%20a%20consultant%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20reported%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20%2412.1%20million.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bmetzger%40insider.com%20(Bryan%20Metzger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A244%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpam-bondi-truth-social-stock-lobbying-financial-disclosure-2025-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Mulholland%20Drive'%20And%20'Twin%20Peaks'%20Director%20David%20Lynch%20Dies%20At%2078%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDavid%20Lynch%20--%20the%20singular%20and%20surreal%20director%20of%20%26quot%3BMulholland%20Drive%26quot%3B%20and%20television's%20%26quot%3BTwin%20Peaks%2C%26quot%3B%20who%20depicted%20the%20darkness%20lurking%20beneath%20the%20wholesome%20surface%20of%20American%20life%20--%20has%20died.%20He%20was%2078%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20enigmatic%20artist%20who%20turned%20his%20hand%20to%20arthouse%20and%20blockbuster%20film%2C%20television%2C%20painting%20and%20music%2C%20Lynch%20was%20considered%20first%20and%20foremost%20one%20of%20US%20cinema's%20great%20auteurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20with%20deep%20regret%20that%20we%2C%20his%20family%2C%20announce%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20man%20and%20the%20artist%2C%20David%20Lynch%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20a%20statement%20on%20his%20official%20Facebook%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20big%20hole%20in%20the%20world%20now%20that%20he's%20no%20longer%20with%20us.%20But%2C%20as%20he%20would%20say%2C%20'Keep%20your%20eye%20on%20the%20donut%20and%20not%20on%20the%20hole.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cause%20and%20location%20of%20death%20were%20not%20specified.%20Lynch%2C%20who%20lived%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20had%20suffered%20from%20emphysema%20after%20years%20of%20heavy%20smoking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20emerged%20on%20the%20US%20indie%20scene%20with%20his%20groundbreaking%201977%20horror%20%26quot%3BEraserhead%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20creepy%20and%20now%20cult%20classic%20shot%20on%20a%20shoestring%20budget%20over%20five%20years%20because%20he%20kept%20running%20out%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%20acquired%20a%20devoted%20following%20with%20critically%20adored%20films%20including%20sadomasochist%20mystery%20%26quot%3BBlue%20Velvet%26quot%3B%20(1986)%20and%20surreal%20thriller%20%26quot%3BMulholland%20Drive%26quot%3B%20(2001).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20may%20be%20best%20remembered%20for%20his%20mesmerizing%201990s%20series%20%26quot%3BTwin%20Peaks%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20many%20a%20prestige%20television%20drama%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20four%20Oscar%20nominations%2C%20including%20a%20trio%20of%20best%20director%20nods%2C%20the%20filmmaker%20recognizable%20by%20his%20shock%20of%20white%20hair%20took%20home%20just%20one%20honorary%20statuette%2C%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20'Fearless'%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETributes%20from%20across%20Hollywood%20were%20swiftly%20posted%20to%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%23RIPDavidLynch%2C%20a%20gracious%20man%20and%20fearless%20artist%20who%20followed%20his%20heart%20%26amp%3B%20soul%20and%20proved%20that%20radical%20experimentation%20could%20yield%20unforgettable%20cinema%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20director%20Ron%20Howard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDavid%20Lynch%2C%20RIP.%20At%20least%20that's%20what%20the%20horse%20wearing%20a%20fez%20just%20told%20me*%20in%20a%20dream.%20(*Backwards%20and%20in%20Swedish)%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20comedian%20and%20actor%20Patton%20Oswalt%2C%20in%20a%20nod%20to%20Lynch's%20highly%20surreal%20style.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%20small-town%20Montana%20in%201946%2C%20the%20son%20of%20a%20US%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20research%20scientist%2C%20Lynch%20travelled%20extensively%20around%20Middle%20America%20as%20a%20young%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20attended%20fine%20arts%20colleges%20in%20both%20Boston%20and%20Philadelphia%2C%20where%20he%20studied%20painting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20one-minute%20animated%20film%20caught%20the%20eye%20of%20the%20American%20Film%20Institute%2C%20where%20he%20began%20work%20on%20what%20would%20later%20become%20%26quot%3BEraserhead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20followed%20by%201980's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Elephant%20Man%2C%26quot%3B%20also%20shot%20in%20black-and-white%20and%20deeply%20tragic%2C%20but%20decidedly%20more%20mainstream%20and%20accessible.%20Lynch%20earned%20his%20first%20best%20director%20Oscar%20nomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20diary%20of%20Joseph%20Merrick%2C%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3BElephant%20Man%26quot%3B%20born%20in%20the%20United%20States%20in%201862%20with%20a%20condition%20that%20gave%20him%20a%20severely%20deformed%20physical%20appearance%2C%20it%20starred%20Anthony%20Hopkins%20and%20John%20Hurt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20attempt%20to%20adapt%20sci-fi%20novel%20%26quot%3BDune%26quot%3B%20into%20a%20blockbuster%20in%201984%20would%20be%20one%20of%20Lynch's%20less%20well-received%20efforts%2C%20though%20it%20still%20has%20its%20admirers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%20pivoted%20back%20to%20his%20arthouse%20roots%20with%20%26quot%3BBlue%20Velvet%2C%26quot%3B%20about%20a%20young%20man%20who%20comes%20home%20from%20college%20and%20finds%20a%20severed%20ear.%20His%20investigation%20uncovers%20the%20sinister%20side%20of%20small-town%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20starred%20Isabella%20Rossellini%20and%20Dennis%20Hopper%2C%20along%20with%20his%20regular%20collaborators%20Kyle%20MacLachlan%20and%20Laura%20Dern%2C%20and%20is%20often%20heralded%20as%20his%20greatest%20work.%20It%20also%20earned%20Lynch's%20second%20Academy%20Award%20nomination%20for%20directing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20winning%20the%20top%20prize%20Palme%20d'Or%20at%20Cannes%20with%20%26quot%3BWild%20at%20Heart%26quot%3B%20in%201990%2C%20Lynch%20turned%20his%20attention%20to%20television%20with%20%26quot%3BTwin%20Peaks%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20captivated%20and%20shocked%20American%20in%20equal%20measure%20from%20its%201990%20launch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tale%20of%20a%20tight-knit%20northwestern%20town%20reacting%20to%20the%20rape%20and%20murder%20of%20a%20popular%20but%20troubled%20high%20school%20girl%2C%20it%20was%20years%20ahead%20of%20its%20time%20and%20far%20more%20sophisticated%20than%20most%20network%20programming%20even%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20ratings%20plummeted%20as%20the%20show's%20second%20season%20lost%20its%20direction%20after%20the%20purported%20meddling%20of%20ABC%20executives%2C%20and%20was%20cancelled.%20An%20even%20darker%201992%20prequel%20film%20was%20initially%20panned%20by%20critics%2C%20but%20is%20now%20considered%20a%20classic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20'Singular%20and%20irreplaceable'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20returning%20to%20film%20with%20%26quot%3BLost%20Highway%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Straight%20Story%2C%26quot%3B%20Lynch%20in%202001%20made%20his%20second%20undisputed%20masterpiece%2C%20%26quot%3BMulholland%20Drive%2C%20which%20brought%20Lynch%20his%20third%20best%20director%20Oscar%20nomination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20baffling%20world%20of%20hallucinations%20and%20cryptic%20happenings%2C%20Naomi%20Watts%20plays%20a%20naive%20actress%20who%20meets%20a%20mysterious%20brunette%20suffering%20amnesia%2C%20before%20everything%20gets%20inverted%20in%20an%20astonishing%20twist%20that%20still%20has%20fans%20arguing%20over%20its%20meaning%20to%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFilm%20writer%20David%20Thomson%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20greatest%20films%20ever%20made%20about%20the%20cultural%20devastation%20caused%20by%20Hollywood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch's%20final%20full-length%20feature%20film%20was%202006's%20inscrutable%20%26quot%3BInland%20Empire%2C%26quot%3B%20although%20he%20returned%20to%20the%20world%20of%20%26quot%3BTwin%20Peaks%26quot%3B%20with%20an%20acclaimed%20sequel%20series%20for%20cable%20network%20Showtime%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20never%20retired%2C%20continuing%20to%20produce%20short%20films%2C%20music%20and%20paintings%20from%20his%20studio%20and%20home%20--%20appropriately%20located%20just%20outside%20Hollywood%2C%20on%20Mulholland%20Drive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20regularly%20posted%20whimsical%20weather%20updates%20to%20his%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20underlining%20the%20optimistic%20and%20playful%20man%20behind%20his%20often%20troubling%20art.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20beautiful%20day%20with%20golden%20sunshine%20and%20blue%20skies%20all%20the%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20his%20family's%20tribute%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20join%20you%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20this%20grief%2C%20in%20love%20and%20in%20reverence%20and%20celebration%20of%20someone%20who%20is%20singular%20and%20irreplaceable