0learning%20opportunities%20to%20help%20employees%20keep%20up%20with%20new%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20discussed%20the%20trend%20toward%20skills-focused%20hiring%20and%20talent%20management%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20also%20emphasized%20the%20challenges%20of%20executing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20can%20be%20a%20difference%20between%20larger%20organizations%20that%20have%20been%20focused%20on%20this%20for%20a%20while%20versus%20midsize%20and%20smaller%20companies%20that%20perhaps%20are%20just%20starting%20that%20journey%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Purvi%20Tailor%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20human%20resources%20at%20Ferring%20Pharmaceuticals%20USA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJack%20Azagury%2C%20the%20group%20chief%20executive%20for%20consulting%20at%20Accenture%2C%20shared%20his%20company's%20experience%20implementing%20skills-based%20HR%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20it%20had%20to%20retrain%20more%20than%20100%2C000%20employees%20on%20cloud%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20on%20the%20journey%20for%20about%2010%20years%20on%20skills-based%20HR%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20took%20a%20while%20to%20get%20it%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20roundtable%20participants%20were%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAnant%20Adya%2C%20executive%20vice%20president%2C%20service%20offering%20head%2C%20and%20head%20of%20Americas%20delivery%2C%20Infosys%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJack%20Azagury%2C%20group%20chief%20executive%20for%20consulting%2C%20Accenture%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELucrecia%20Borgonovo%2C%20chief%20talent%20and%20organizational%20effectiveness%20officer%2C%20Mastercard%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKenon%20Chen%2C%20executive%20vice%20president%20of%20strategy%20and%20growth%2C%20Clear%20Capital%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMaggie%20Hulce%2C%20chief%20revenue%20officer%2C%20Indeed%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShane%20Koller%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20and%20chief%20people%20officer%2C%20Ancestry%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJustina%20Nixon-Saintil%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20chief%20impact%20officer%2C%20IBM%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMarjorie%20Powell%2C%20chief%20HR%20officer%20and%20senior%20vice%20president%2C%20AARP%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPurvi%20Tailor%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20human%20resources%2C%20Ferring%20Pharmaceuticals%20USA%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESharawn%20Tipton%2C%20chief%20people%20and%20culture%20officer%2C%20LiveRamp%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERebecca%20Knight%3A%20What%20do%20you%20predict%20will%20be%20the%20single%20most%20important%20change%20in%20the%20workforce%20in%202025%3F%20And%20what%20advice%20do%20you%20have%20for%20business%20leaders%20to%20prepare%20themselves%20for%20that%20change%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286886746-d4db-4aaa-881a-cf96e58374bc%5C%22%3EAI%20search%2C%20workflows%2C%20and%20ethics%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKenon%20Chen%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI've%20been%20thinking%20about%20this%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it'll%20have%20a%20really%20large%20impact%2C%20which%20is%20the%20idea%20of%20an%20AI-first%20search.%20This%20is%20where%20the%20search%20funnel%20is%20providing%20direct%20answers%20as%20opposed%20to%20just%20a%20ranked%20set%20of%20results.%20I%20think%20of%20it%20as%20summary-before-source%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20number%20of%20companies%20looking%20at%20adopting%20this%20technology%20in-house%20as%20a%20way%20of%20modernizing%20the%20knowledge%20base%20and%20providing%20employees%20with%20direct%20searchable%20information%20to%20do%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20really%20changes%20the%20historical%20barriers%20to%20accessing%20subject-matter%20expertise%20within%20a%20company.%20To%20access%20someone%20who%20used%20to%20be%20the%20owner%20of%20that%20data%20or%20the%20one%20who%20knew%20the%20most%20about%20that%20subject%2C%20you%20had%20to%20engage%20their%20time.%20In%20this%20new%20world%2C%20you%20can%20bypass%20all%20of%20that%20and%20get%20an%20answer.%20But%20it%20might%20not%20be%20the%20most%20accurate%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20leveraged%20well%2C%20I%20think%20companies%20can%20actually%20have%20a%20really%20strong%20competitive%20advantage%2C%20because%20making%20data%20more%20available%20to%20employees%20can%20help%20people%20have%20shared%20goals%20and%20derive%20their%20value%20from%20achieving%20that%20shared%20goal%20together%20as%20opposed%20to%20just%20managing%20data%20currency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJustina%20Nixon-Saintil%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThere's%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20talk%20about%20AI%20agents.%20I%20think%20there%20are%20two%20areas%20that%20companies%20have%20to%20really%20focus%20on%20for%202025.%20One%20is%20how%20do%20you%20balance%20innovation%20versus%20executing%20some%20of%20these%20AI%20systems%20in%20the%20most%20responsible%20way%3F%20And%20I%20think%20both%20of%20them%20are%20tied%20to%20ethical%20AI%20and%20skills%20building.%20Focusing%20on%20upskilling%20your%20employees%20and%20making%20sure%20you%20have%20a%20skilled%20talent%20pipeline%20in%20AI%20will%20be%20critical%20for%20employers%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20thing%20is%20the%20ethical%20responsibilities%20that%20companies%20have.%20When%20you're%20providing%20a%20prompt%20for%20a%20system%20to%20execute%20something%2C%20you%20really%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20implications%20of%20that.%20What%20are%20the%20types%20of%20guardrails%20that%20you%20have%20to%20put%20in%20place%20to%20be%20able%20to%20use%20AI%20agents%20effectively%20and%20also%20safeguard%20your%20company%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaggie%20Hulce%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThere%20are%20incremental%20projects%20in%20particular%20functions%20that%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20make%20workflows%20better.%20Then%20there%20are%20the%20reimagination%20projects%20of%20how%20should%20this%20customer%20journey%20be%20radically%20different%20if%20AI%20can%20drive%20all%20of%20these%20steps%3F%20And%20it%20cuts%20across%20many%20people's%20ownership%20lines%20and%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrganizationally%2C%20how%20do%20you%20make%20sure%20there's%20a%20group%20of%20people%20set%20up%20and%20empowered%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20think%20about%20problems%20that%20would%20shake%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20with%20a%20clean%20sheet%20of%20paper%26quot%3B%3F%20I%20think%20if%20we%20leave%20it%20for%20each%20function%20to%20sort%20out%20when%20it's%20that%20loaded%20across%20functions%2C%20it's%20too%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECulturally%2C%20how%20do%20we%20reward%20innovation%20and%20adaptability%20and%20let%20people%20embrace%20change%3F%20How%20do%20you%20reward%20and%20reinforce%20a%20culture%20that%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20figured%20out%20how%20we%20could%20do%20this%20translation%20thing%20totally%20differently.%20Don't%20worry%20that%20we%20need%20to%20retrain%20the%20manual%20translation%20team%3B%20we%20will%20retrain%20them.%20Think%20about%20what%20can%20and%20should%20be%20changed%20with%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bec29e5-4b61-4cb4-ac5f-a558d602ce2b%5C%22%3ELifelong%20learning%20and%20upskilling%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMarjorie%20Powell%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20workforce%20is%20continually%20being%20driven%20by%20the%20aging%20of%20the%20population%20and%20the%20growing%20prominence%20of%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20you%20saw%20more%20people%20over%2065%20choosing%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20workforce%20than%20ever%20before%2C%20partly%20because%20of%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-regrets-saving-investing-loneliness-parenting-older-americans-survey-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econcerns%20about%20retirement%20security%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%20employers%20are%20going%20to%20have%20to%20adapt%20by%20creating%20age-inclusive%20workplaces.%20They're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20harness%20the%20experience%20and%20the%20skills%20of%20older%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20going%20to%20mean%20that%20we%20have%20to%20rethink%20traditional%20career%20trajectories%20and%20offer%20flexible%20work%20arrangements.%20We're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20invest%20in%20lifelong%20learning%20opportunities%20for%20older%20workers%2C%20keep%20them%20engaged%2C%20and%20keep%20them%20invested%20in%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShane%20Koller%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThis%20is%20a%20key%20area%20where%20the%20HR%20function%20can%20and%20should%20influence%20companies%20going%20forward.%20What%20I%20see%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20even%20with%20employees%20who%20are%20relatively%20tech-savvy%2C%20is%20that%20it%20feels%20like%20they're%20stuck%20right%20now%20on%20what%20next%20step%20they%20need%20to%20take%20to%20be%20along%20with%20the%20ride%20versus%20being%20left%20behind.%20This%20is%20where%20we%20as%20a%20function%20have%20to%20really%20get%20out%20of%20neutral%20and%20help%20the%20workforce%20understand%20what%20those%20next%20steps%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENixon-Saintil%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELifelong%20learning%20doesn't%20just%20end%20with%20AI.%20You%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20acceleration%20of%20technology.%20How%20do%20we%20make%20sure%20people%20understand%20that%20every%20new%20wave%20of%20technology%20will%20demand%20new%20skills%20and%20that%20lifelong%20learners%20will%20thrive%3F%20This%20has%20to%20be%20a%20complete%20mindset%20change%20for%20employees%20and%20employers%20from%20an%20investment%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20thing%2C%20just%20with%20my%20social-responsibility%20hat%20on%2C%20is%20how%20do%20we%20make%20sure%20we're%20investing%20in%20populations%20and%20providing%20them%20with%20access%20to%20free%20skilling%2C%20mentors%2C%20and%20real%20learning%20experiences%20so%20that%20they%20can%20be%20prepared%3F%20How%20do%20we%20build%20that%20talent%20pipeline%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20something%20we%20are%20doing%20through%20programs%20like%20IBM%20SkillsBuild.%20But%20it's%20overall%20something%20that%20every%20company%20needs%20to%20consider%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20investing%20in%20your%20employees%20but%20looking%20at%20universities%2C%20K-12%20systems%2C%20and%20partnerships%20with%20nonprofit%20organizations%20that%20focus%20on%20marginalized%20groups%20and%20provide%20free%20access%20to%20these%20new%20skills%20and%20technologies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f1613a3a-3ea1-446f-8b36-8d1c5fff9e52%5C%22%3ESkills-based%20talent%20management%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnant%20Adya%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI'm%20a%20big%20believer%20that%20skills%20are%20more%20important%20than%20the%20four-year%20college%20degrees%20that%20everybody%20runs%20after.%20We%20recruit%20a%20lot%20from%20underrepresented%20communities%20and%20communities%20in%20general%20where%20we%20do%20not%20look%20for%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20we%20are%20going%20to%20announce%20some%20sort%20of%20target%20for%20ourselves%20where%20we%20say%20that%20X%20percentage%20of%20our%20population%20is%20going%20to%20come%20from%20skills%20and%20not%20from%20four-year%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESharawn%20Tipton%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20also%20see%20skills-based%20talent%20management%20as%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20trends%20for%202025.%20We%20talk%20a%20lot%20about%20experience%20and%20what%20people%20have%20in%20their%20tool%20kits%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20about%20skill%20and%20learning%20agility%2C%20because%20the%20technology%20is%20moving%20so%20quickly%20that%20you%20have%20to%20work%20in%20a%20different%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJack%20Azagury%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESkills-based%20HR%20is%20a%20very%20complex%20area.%20The%20first%20pointer%20I'd%20give%20is%20to%20start%20in%20one%20place%2C%20not%20the%20entire%20enterprise%2C%20and%20pilot%20and%20get%20the%20algorithms.%20It%20took%20us%20years%20to%20get%20the%20right%20algorithm%20to%20determine%20what%20skills%20somebody%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20is%20to%20be%20very%20transparent%20about%20how%20you're%20measuring%20skills.%20For%20example%2C%20our%20algorithm%20says%20you%20need%20to%20have%20worked%20on%20this%20type%20of%20job%20for%20this%20amount%20of%20months%2C%20and%20that%20job%20cannot%20be%20more%20than%20six%20months%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20thing%20I%20would%20say%20is%20do%20not%20use%20skills-based%20HR%20for%20cost%20reduction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20is%20employees%20need%20to%20see%20how%20you're%20going%20to%20use%20skills-based%20HR%20%E2%80%94%20how%20you're%20going%20to%20give%20people%20new%20opportunities%2C%20training%2C%20and%20development.%20They%20need%20to%20see%20the%20positive%20coming%20out%20for%20their%20careers%20in%20your%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELucrecia%20Borgonovo%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20biggest%20change%20is%20definitely%20going%20to%20be%20around%20skills-powered%20organizations.%20We%20know%20that%20there's%20not%20necessarily%20a%20playbook%20and%20we%20have%20to%20cocreate%20this%20playbook%20together.%20I%20think%20this%20requires%20pretty%20significant%20change%20management%20in%20addition%20to%20tech%20enablement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20say%20to%20our%20leaders%20at%20Mastercard%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20you're%20taking%20on%20a%20much%20more%20enterprise-wide%20versus%20siloed%20approach%20when%20you%20think%20about%20talent%20and%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20an%20employee%20standpoint%2C%20we%20were%20talking%20about%20learning%20agility%20as%20a%20huge%20currency.%20You%20want%20to%20have%20employees%20who%20are%20curious%2C%20open%2C%20and%20adaptable%20and%20who%20could%20be%20much%20more%20fundable%20in%20this%20incredibly%20changing%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChen%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20best%20way%20to%20prepare%20for%20change%20and%20transformation%20is%20to%20ensure%20your%20fundamentals%20are%20in%20place.%20There's%20a%20reason%20sports%20teams%2C%20musicians%2C%20and%20other%20folks%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20master%20a%20new%20skill%20often%20go%20back%20to%20make%20sure%20their%20fundamentals%20are%20really%20solid%20so%20they%20have%20a%20foundation%20to%20build%20upon%20for%20something%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20thinking%20about%20that%20a%20lot%20for%20AI%20and%20skills-based%20HR.%20If%20the%20basics%20%E2%80%94%20things%20like%20transparency%2C%20communication%2C%20shared%20mission%2C%20purpose%2C%20and%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20aren't%20in%20place%2C%20it's%20really%20difficult%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20radical%20transformation.%20The%20speed%20all%20this%20is%20moving%20at%20is%20so%20rapid%20that%20it's%20impossible%20to%20predict%20exactly%20how%20this%20might%20play%20out.%20But%20if%20the%20fundamentals%20are%20in%20place%2C%20you%20can%20weather%20those%20unknowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-share-top-3-predictions-for-the-workforce-in-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1737060574000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67894c902fcded5e90738333%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-share-top-3-predictions-for-the-workforce-in-2025-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Workforce%20Innovation%20board%20members%20discussed%20the%20trends%20they%20expect%20to%20see%20in%202025%20and%20the%20advice%20they'd%20give%20business%20leaders%20to%20prepare%20for%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jean%20Paik)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A61%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-share-top-3-predictions-fo