d%20the%20yuan%20become%20more%20competitive%20with%20other%20EM%20currencies%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20tariffs%20on%20China%20would%20thus%20likely%20only%20grow%20the%20country's%20existing%20export%20volume%2C%20hurting%20EM%20countries'%20production%20and%20capex%20in%20the%20process%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTariffs%20may%20be%20inflationary%20for%20the%20US%2C%20but%20the%20opposite%20will%20be%20true%20for%20those%20economies%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETariffs%20could%20also%20help%20accelerate%20a%20slowdown%20in%20China's%20imports%2C%20too%2C%20as%20the%20country%20faces%20weaker%20profitability%20and%20fiscal%20headwinds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20an%20effect%20would%20continue%20to%20pose%20a%20drag%20on%20manufacturing%20competitors%20and%20also%20start%20hitting%20EM%20commodity%20exporters%2C%20too%2C%20he%20says%2C%20with%20little%20relief%20from%20the%20country's%20drastic%20stimulus%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFiscal%20stimulus%20won't%20compensate%2C%20in%20our%20view.%20That%20is%20tilting%20towards%20consumption%20%E2%80%94%20positive%20for%20the%20consumer%20and%20internet%20companies%20that%20dominate%20Chinese%20stocks%20%E2%80%94%20but%20with%20little%20spillover%20to%20broader%20emerging%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmerging%20markets%20are%20increasingly%20vulnerable%20to%20a%20potential%20trade%20war%20given%20their%20slowing%20growth%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20with%20investment%20as%20a%20share%20of%20GDP%20currently%20stuck%20at%202008%20levels.%20Plus%2C%20tariff-sensitive%20sectors%20like%20autos%2C%20steel%20and%20infrastructure%20compose%20a%20higher%20share%20of%20EM%20stocks%2C%20and%20those%20outside%20of%20China%20are%20historically%20expensive%20despite%20flat%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENarain%20sees%20countries%20like%20Mexico%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20Taiwan%2C%20Korea%2C%20and%20Thailand%20as%20likely%20targets%20for%20further%20tariffs%20given%20their%20rela